WEBVTT

00:01.209 --> 00:03.378
[♪ opening theme song playing]

01:41.100 --> 01:42.436
[tapping on pen]

01:42.477 --> 01:44.271
Did I tell you I own a cat?

01:45.814 --> 01:47.066
You were saying?

01:47.942 --> 01:50.069
[OE] This cop suddenly
started speaking to me.

01:50.861 --> 01:52.905
Then there were two,
and then three of them.

01:53.405 --> 01:54.656
And I thought,
"If they take me in now,

01:54.698 --> 01:56.366
my cat's gonna die."

01:57.242 --> 01:59.244
My place doesn't allow pets.

01:59.578 --> 02:00.662
So you see,

02:01.080 --> 02:02.831
I'm the only one
who knows about it.

02:02.873 --> 02:05.709
[HIGURUMA] In Morioka City,
Iwate Prefecture,

02:05.751 --> 02:07.920
in March of 2016,

02:07.962 --> 02:10.297
two people, a young girl
and her mother,

02:10.338 --> 02:12.716
were found fatally stabbed
in their own home.

02:13.132 --> 02:16.344
The Morioka Prosecutors Office
indicted Keita Oe,

02:16.386 --> 02:18.179
who lived near the crime scene.

02:18.221 --> 02:20.891
He was charged
with felony murder and robbery.

02:21.433 --> 02:23.811
The events leading
to his arrest were thus.

02:23.852 --> 02:26.814
While being questioned
by three officers on patrol,

02:26.855 --> 02:28.732
Keita Oe suddenly fled.

02:28.774 --> 02:30.901
The patrolmen chased Oe
to his home.

02:31.401 --> 02:33.194
Once inside,
the officers discovered

02:33.236 --> 02:34.822
a knife covered in blood.

02:35.238 --> 02:37.825
Oe was arrested
in flagrante delicto.

02:38.450 --> 02:39.534
[PATROLMAN 1] He's in here!

02:39.576 --> 02:41.662
[HIGURUMA] After DNA analysis,

02:41.703 --> 02:43.162
the blood
on the blade was revealed

02:43.204 --> 02:45.206
to be a match
to the victim's DNA.

02:45.248 --> 02:46.333
[slams]

02:46.374 --> 02:49.044
Oe consistently
denied all charges.

02:49.086 --> 02:51.588
Asked to explain the knife,
he insisted...

02:52.089 --> 02:53.507
[OE] I just picked it up.

02:53.882 --> 02:55.300
It wasn't mine.

02:55.342 --> 02:57.803
A little hard to believe,
don't you think so?

02:58.053 --> 03:00.263
He didn't flee questioning
because of his cat,

03:00.305 --> 03:02.141
he fled because he was guilty.

03:02.181 --> 03:03.517
[HIGURUMA] I don't think so.

03:03.558 --> 03:06.394
He had been wrongly detained
by the police before,

03:06.436 --> 03:09.815
when an acquaintance of his
was busted for using drugs.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.984
You're saying the police
traumatized him?

03:12.026 --> 03:14.444
But even so, "I picked it up"?

03:14.486 --> 03:16.237
Who picks up a bloody knife?

03:16.279 --> 03:17.196
No one.

03:17.739 --> 03:19.533
[HIGURUMA] He claims
he was planning to turn it

03:19.574 --> 03:21.035
into the police later.

03:21.076 --> 03:22.327
"Later"?

03:23.202 --> 03:24.705
[HIGURUMA] I know, I know.

03:24.746 --> 03:26.623
His claims are all hard
to believe.

03:26.999 --> 03:29.084
But when you consider
Oe's background,

03:29.126 --> 03:31.210
the fact he works
as a live-in employee

03:31.252 --> 03:33.088
at a non-profit organisation,

03:33.130 --> 03:35.423
it definitely starts sounding
plausible to me.

03:35.966 --> 03:37.425
What kind of non-profit?

03:38.593 --> 03:40.345
[HIGURUMA]
A shelter for the elderly

03:40.387 --> 03:41.805
who have nowhere else to go.

03:41.847 --> 03:44.391
They provide support
for their independent living.

03:44.432 --> 03:46.393
Oe's job was taking care
of the residents

03:46.434 --> 03:47.477
who lived there.

03:47.811 --> 03:50.189
However, they didn't pay him
a salary with wages.

03:50.229 --> 03:51.773
They only supplied him
with goods

03:51.815 --> 03:54.275
like groceries, boxed lunches,

03:54.317 --> 03:57.029
and gifts of pocket money
for New Year's sometimes.

03:57.571 --> 03:58.989
And if you could believe it,

03:59.031 --> 04:01.533
they still charged him
50,000 yen a month

04:01.575 --> 04:02.951
for rent on his room.

04:02.993 --> 04:04.119
[SHIMIZU] Brutal.

04:04.161 --> 04:06.205
Apparently, quite a few
of the residents

04:06.245 --> 04:07.581
have prior records.

04:08.207 --> 04:10.375
Anyway, when asked
why he didn't turn in the knife

04:10.417 --> 04:11.543
as soon as he found it...

04:11.585 --> 04:14.088
The rules say
we can't call cop cars.

04:14.129 --> 04:15.463
Or ambulances either.

04:16.131 --> 04:18.675
They don't want loud sirens
bothering the neighbors.

04:20.135 --> 04:22.888
[SHIMIZU] That non-profit
sounds pretty suspicious.

04:22.930 --> 04:23.889
[HIGURUMA] Yeah.

04:24.181 --> 04:26.600
It's extremely close
to being outright illegal.

04:26.641 --> 04:28.102
Since the earthquake
relief funds

04:28.143 --> 04:29.853
started flowing
into this region,

04:29.895 --> 04:33.148
we've seen an increase
in suspiciously managed NPOs.

04:34.273 --> 04:35.316
So it's possible

04:35.442 --> 04:37.569
the murder weapon
was just lying there.

04:38.112 --> 04:41.240
I think there's a good chance
that Oe is innocent.

04:43.075 --> 04:44.283
First, we'll investigate

04:44.325 --> 04:46.620
the organization's activities
and tax filings.

04:46.661 --> 04:49.164
Then run background checks
on all the residents.

04:49.456 --> 04:51.833
I'll focus on getting
more information out of Oe.

04:51.875 --> 04:53.919
You handle
the investigation, Shimizu.

04:53.961 --> 04:56.046
[SHIMIZU] You're dumping
a huge job like that on me

04:56.088 --> 04:57.256
out of the blue?

04:57.756 --> 04:58.840
[door opens]

04:59.298 --> 05:00.968
[HIGURUMA] And could you
take care of his cat?

05:01.009 --> 05:02.136
[SHIMIZU] His cat?

05:02.761 --> 05:05.430
The commission on
a public defender case is zilch,

05:05.472 --> 05:07.224
no matter how many hours
we bill.

05:07.266 --> 05:09.517
And the public always
assumes they're guilty.

05:09.559 --> 05:12.146
Plus, there's no suspended
sentence in murder cases.

05:12.187 --> 05:14.106
So he could get
the death penalty.

05:14.148 --> 05:16.483
There's nothing to gain
by taking this case.

05:16.942 --> 05:19.111
Higuruma, will you
please explain to me

05:19.153 --> 05:21.822
why you go around
accepting cases like this one?

05:21.863 --> 05:23.240
It's good once in a while.

05:23.740 --> 05:26.367
If we stuck to easy work,
our skills would dull.

05:26.409 --> 05:28.954
[SHIMIZU] It's more
than once in a while.

05:28.996 --> 05:30.789
It's more than once in a while!

05:30.831 --> 05:33.125
[HIGURUMA] You're saying
your thoughts out loud again.

05:34.001 --> 05:35.585
[Takagi laughs]

05:35.627 --> 05:38.463
Sounds like Higuruma
hasn't changed a bit, then.

05:39.506 --> 05:41.424
It's tough working for
an independent lawyer

05:41.466 --> 05:43.051
who isn't in it for the money.

05:43.593 --> 05:45.512
[SHIMIZU] Yeah, well,
at least I'm not stuck

05:45.553 --> 05:47.931
having to run a cafe
on the side like you are.

05:48.431 --> 05:49.390
Hey, wait a minute.

05:49.432 --> 05:50.851
When you say he hasn't changed,

05:50.892 --> 05:52.853
you mean Higuruma's
always been like this?

05:52.894 --> 05:54.562
Hm? Not really.

05:55.189 --> 05:57.524
I think he actually
used to be a lot worse.

05:57.858 --> 05:58.859
[SHIMIZU] Huh?

05:59.276 --> 06:00.861
[TAKAGI]
Back when he was with us,

06:00.902 --> 06:02.946
he was in charge
of a reckless driving case

06:02.988 --> 06:04.656
that resulted in injury.

06:04.698 --> 06:06.825
Specifically,
it was for drunk driving.

06:07.366 --> 06:09.328
The defendant was only 19.

06:09.368 --> 06:10.829
And his co-workers
had coerced him

06:10.871 --> 06:12.706
into doing
both the drinking part

06:12.747 --> 06:14.457
and the driving part.

06:14.499 --> 06:17.627
However, those involved
all aligned their stories,

06:17.669 --> 06:19.880
and he didn't have the money
for a settlement,

06:19.921 --> 06:22.549
and we couldn't get him
a suspended sentence.

06:22.590 --> 06:25.177
[tires screech, crashes]

06:27.346 --> 06:28.429
[CLIENT] You liar!

06:28.471 --> 06:30.389
[breathing heavily]

06:30.431 --> 06:33.018
You promised me
they would find me innocent!

06:33.768 --> 06:36.313
You promised to get
him a suspended sentence,

06:36.355 --> 06:37.647
not an innocent verdict.

06:37.856 --> 06:40.275
Although you didn't manage
to do either, so there's that.

06:40.317 --> 06:42.319
You know what
the takeaway from this is?

06:42.361 --> 06:45.655
Quit being a criminal defense
lawyer for impossible cases.

06:45.697 --> 06:47.991
Trying to save the weak
may be a noble endeavor,

06:48.033 --> 06:49.910
but there's a limit
to what lawyers like us can do

06:49.951 --> 06:52.913
without any cooperation
from the courts and prosecutors.

06:52.954 --> 06:55.207
They don't wanna sit
and hear a client's sob story.

06:55.249 --> 06:57.000
They just wanna
clear their dockets.

06:57.042 --> 06:59.878
It's not worth continuing
when your clients resent you.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.963
[laughing]

07:02.005 --> 07:03.798
[HIGURUMA] They're at the end
of their rope,

07:03.840 --> 07:05.717
both mentally and financially.

07:06.260 --> 07:08.427
I can't blame them
for lashing out at me.

07:11.098 --> 07:12.057
[TAKAGI] But, Higuruma,

07:12.557 --> 07:14.351
what about your mental state?

07:15.394 --> 07:16.603
[HIGURUMA] Well, I'm...

07:18.897 --> 07:20.439
[♪ percussion music playing]

07:27.114 --> 07:28.407
[inaudible]

07:35.454 --> 07:37.665
[snoring softly]

07:38.792 --> 07:41.295
[JUDGE] We the People,
find the defendant...

07:41.878 --> 07:42.879
innocent.

07:42.921 --> 07:45.464
[hushed chatter]

07:45.673 --> 07:47.050
[gasps]

07:48.551 --> 07:50.595
We actually won this case?

07:52.555 --> 07:53.890
[HIGURUMA] Not yet.

07:55.183 --> 07:56.935
They'll appeal right away.

08:02.690 --> 08:04.151
The prosecution is appealing...

08:05.526 --> 08:06.569
[camera clicks]

08:13.243 --> 08:14.702
[SHIMIZU] After the police
searched your room

08:14.744 --> 08:15.787
for stolen items,

08:15.829 --> 08:17.080
nothing was found there.

08:17.622 --> 08:19.874
And in the same
non-profit residence,

08:19.916 --> 08:21.084
another person went missing

08:21.126 --> 08:22.710
right after
the crime was committed.

08:23.128 --> 08:25.213
Luckily, you were caught
on the security feed

08:25.255 --> 08:26.465
of a convenience store.

08:26.505 --> 08:28.507
That and the condition
of the corpses proved

08:28.549 --> 08:30.802
you couldn't have been
at the scene of the murders.

08:30.844 --> 08:32.637
[chuckles] Boy,
it's a good thing

08:32.679 --> 08:34.597
you don't know
how to cook for yourself.

08:34.973 --> 08:36.183
Higuruma, sir.

08:36.641 --> 08:38.435
I wanna thank you
for everything.

08:38.935 --> 08:40.812
There's no need
to call me "sir."

08:41.313 --> 08:42.939
We're not in the clear yet.

08:42.981 --> 08:44.399
There's still the appeal.

08:45.859 --> 08:47.235
That's not what I mean.

08:49.863 --> 08:51.739
You're the only one
who believed me.

08:51.781 --> 08:52.866
Thank you.

09:02.417 --> 09:04.002
[HIGURUMA] While
defense lawyers have to work

09:04.044 --> 09:06.338
with limited budgets
and manpower,

09:06.380 --> 09:08.382
prosecutors can use
taxpayer money

09:08.423 --> 09:11.218
to pour on the lawyers
and dig up the evidence.

09:11.676 --> 09:12.677
That's fine.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.304
It's how the system works.

09:14.721 --> 09:15.930
However,

09:15.972 --> 09:17.391
the prosecutors didn't submit

09:17.432 --> 09:19.809
any new evidence
during the second trial.

09:20.435 --> 09:22.479
The judge accepted
their absurd claim

09:22.521 --> 09:25.648
that there was no reason
to consider the missing person

09:25.690 --> 09:27.067
as a suspect.

09:27.775 --> 09:29.361
So they overturned the verdict.

09:30.237 --> 09:32.197
The highest court
is always the bottleneck

09:32.239 --> 09:33.781
for a third trial.

09:33.823 --> 09:36.243
Most final appeals
are turned away at the door.

09:36.701 --> 09:39.454
It's challenging to even
get a proper trial there.

09:40.497 --> 09:43.417
This trial was destined
for a guilty verdict

09:43.458 --> 09:44.792
from the start.

09:51.590 --> 09:53.009
Why are you...

09:54.511 --> 09:56.679
looking at me that way?

09:59.766 --> 10:00.975
[TAKAGI] But, Higuruma...

10:02.436 --> 10:03.811
what about your mental state?

10:03.853 --> 10:05.313
[birds chirping]

10:05.355 --> 10:06.940
[HIGURUMA] Well,
I'm not trying to promote

10:06.981 --> 10:09.276
the ideals of saving the weak.

10:09.317 --> 10:11.152
It's just always
gone against my nature

10:11.194 --> 10:13.821
to leave things alone
when I feel like they're wrong.

10:14.322 --> 10:16.699
I've just never been able
to fix that habit.

10:17.576 --> 10:19.494
The goddess of justice
blinds her sight

10:19.536 --> 10:21.496
to maintain fairness
under the law.

10:21.996 --> 10:24.332
And people turn a blind eye
to all kinds of things

10:24.374 --> 10:25.875
to protect themselves.

10:27.294 --> 10:29.421
But I don't wanna brush away
the hands of people

10:29.463 --> 10:31.172
who cling to me for help.

10:34.968 --> 10:37.845
The least I can do
is keep my eyes open.

10:39.598 --> 10:42.100
[hushed chatter]

10:42.142 --> 10:44.894
[APPELLATE JUDGE] If there are
any objections to today's trial,

10:44.936 --> 10:48.273
submit your final appeal
in writing within 15 days,

10:48.315 --> 10:50.191
which includes today.

10:50.233 --> 10:53.027
[hushed chatter continues]

10:53.069 --> 10:54.571
[Higuruma sighs]

10:55.905 --> 10:59.451
[gavel banging]

11:01.077 --> 11:03.163
Higuruma, what are you doing?

11:06.374 --> 11:08.168
[HIGURUMA] Everyone come back!

11:08.209 --> 11:09.628
[Shimizu gasps]

11:13.298 --> 11:14.966
We're having a retrial.

11:18.011 --> 11:19.929
- [REMI] Higuruma's in...
- [AMAI] Higuruma's in...

11:20.388 --> 11:22.223
- ...Shinjuku.
- ...Ikebukuro.

11:22.265 --> 11:24.518
- Got it?
- Shinjuku?

11:24.934 --> 11:27.061
I hope Itadori's
headed there, too.

11:27.103 --> 11:28.729
Ikebukuro, huh?

11:28.771 --> 11:30.273
I wonder if Fushiguro's there.

11:33.568 --> 11:36.779
[sighs] Isn't she
running a little late?

11:36.821 --> 11:39.282
That girl better
get here soon or else.

11:39.324 --> 11:41.451
But if she doesn't have
my neck sucker with her,

11:41.493 --> 11:43.244
she'd better not come at all.

11:46.581 --> 11:48.749
- [slaps]
- [man groans]

11:49.959 --> 11:52.753
- [slaps]
- Ow. What's your problem?

11:52.795 --> 11:55.382
[AMAI] No, no, no, no!

11:55.423 --> 11:56.715
We ask the questions!

11:56.757 --> 11:59.010
What are you doing
around here, huh?

11:59.511 --> 12:01.221
This is getting old.

12:01.262 --> 12:03.056
[whimpering]

12:03.097 --> 12:04.807
[AMAI]
Why are you keeping quiet?

12:04.849 --> 12:07.477
You're better off
laughing with us.

12:07.519 --> 12:09.521
[STUDENT 1]
What? You gonna hit me?

12:09.563 --> 12:10.938
- [grunts]
- [students laughing]

12:10.980 --> 12:13.650
[AMAI] Oh, dear.
What did I tell you?

12:14.108 --> 12:16.319
Not that I actually told you.

12:16.361 --> 12:18.363
But why can't you understand?

12:18.405 --> 12:19.822
Are you an idiot?

12:19.864 --> 12:22.576
These guys aren't
that smart or athletic,

12:22.617 --> 12:24.661
but they're brimming with pride.

12:24.703 --> 12:27.163
All you have to do
is just match their attitude

12:27.205 --> 12:28.582
and joke around with them,

12:28.623 --> 12:31.167
so you don't hurt
that ego of theirs.

12:31.209 --> 12:34.170
Then you won't get targeted
by anyone else, either.

12:34.212 --> 12:36.423
And you might even have
a good time now and then.

12:36.464 --> 12:37.340
[girls giggling]

12:37.382 --> 12:39.467
- [YUJI] Knock it off.
- Hmm?

12:40.801 --> 12:41.760
[sighs]

12:42.220 --> 12:43.804
[AMAI]
Here comes another idiot.

12:43.846 --> 12:46.224
[STUDENT 1] Is that uniform
from West Middle?

12:46.266 --> 12:48.017
[chuckles]
You're in middle school?

12:48.059 --> 12:50.228
[STUDENT 2] You need
to learn some respect!

12:50.604 --> 12:52.146
We're gonna teach you a lesson!

12:52.188 --> 12:53.356
[panting]

12:53.398 --> 12:55.108
Down you go!

12:55.149 --> 12:56.192
Huh?

12:56.859 --> 12:58.278
[grunting]

13:01.489 --> 13:02.741
[STUDENT 1] Huh?

13:05.952 --> 13:07.454
[metal rod scraping]

13:09.872 --> 13:12.833
You really shouldn't be
so violent!

13:12.875 --> 13:13.918
[grunts]

13:14.377 --> 13:16.421
[grunting]

13:16.463 --> 13:20.091
- [groans]
- [grunts]

13:20.717 --> 13:23.303
Huh? [groaning]

13:23.886 --> 13:25.138
[groans]

13:25.179 --> 13:27.515
[students coughing and groaning]

13:29.183 --> 13:30.226
[YUJI] And you?

13:31.561 --> 13:33.104
[heart thumping]

13:33.647 --> 13:35.690
Y-you... you mean me?

13:36.733 --> 13:37.776
[MEGUMI] Hey.

13:38.025 --> 13:39.026
[REMI] What now?

13:39.402 --> 13:40.987
[MEGUMI] You aren't planning
to go through Ikebukuro

13:41.028 --> 13:42.572
to reach Shinjuku, are you?

13:43.156 --> 13:44.991
That area's rich
with supplies.

13:45.032 --> 13:46.993
We're more likely
to encounter other players.

13:47.868 --> 13:50.163
[REMI] There are two reasons
for going this way.

13:50.789 --> 13:52.373
The route is easy to follow,

13:52.749 --> 13:55.042
and I happen
to have a base nearby.

13:56.377 --> 13:58.713
I'm just dying
to take a shower.

13:58.755 --> 14:01.591
I haven't had a chance
to rest since yesterday.

14:04.218 --> 14:07.138
[AMAI] Higuruma uses
this theater as his base.

14:07.180 --> 14:08.931
Assuming he hasn't moved,
that is.

14:09.349 --> 14:10.558
Ah, cool.

14:10.600 --> 14:11.934
You've been a big help, man.

14:11.976 --> 14:12.935
Thank you.

14:13.394 --> 14:16.063
Uh, wait a minute.
Hold up, don't go.

14:16.356 --> 14:17.565
[YUJI] Hmm? What is it?

14:17.607 --> 14:19.526
[AMAI]
Uh, you're seriously going in?

14:19.567 --> 14:21.736
[YUJI] Well, I'd have preferred
to go in with my friend,

14:21.778 --> 14:22.821
but I'm in a hurry.

14:23.697 --> 14:26.366
I never actually met
Higuruma myself.

14:26.407 --> 14:29.828
But I once saw him beat Haba
to a pulp right in front of me.

14:29.868 --> 14:31.496
Then I'll totally be okay.

14:31.538 --> 14:33.080
I beat propeller head, too.

14:33.122 --> 14:34.915
Which means I'll
at least be able to run away.

14:34.957 --> 14:35.958
[Amai hesitates]

14:36.959 --> 14:37.960
[YUJI] See you later.

14:38.002 --> 14:39.253
[AMAI] Uh...

14:40.046 --> 14:42.006
- [heart thumping]
- Tell him.

14:42.048 --> 14:44.133
Come on, man, tell him!

14:44.718 --> 14:46.678
You should stop doing this.

14:52.600 --> 14:53.685
I'm sorry...

14:54.227 --> 14:55.228
[door creaks]

14:55.269 --> 14:56.354
...Itadori.

14:58.939 --> 15:01.150
It's about time, Higuruma.

15:01.192 --> 15:02.318
[chuckles]

15:02.610 --> 15:05.988
Sorry, I guess we were
both expecting to see him.

15:06.030 --> 15:07.114
I'm Reggie.

15:07.407 --> 15:09.617
And she deceived you.

15:12.911 --> 15:14.581
Don't give me that look.

15:14.622 --> 15:16.791
You don't scare me for a second.

15:16.833 --> 15:19.168
- And just so you know, Reggie--
- [MEGUMI] Quiet!

15:21.295 --> 15:22.797
[snarls]

15:22.839 --> 15:24.382
[chuckles excitedly]

15:25.966 --> 15:27.802
I'm wasting my time here.

15:38.772 --> 15:40.356
[HIGURUMA] Who's there?

15:40.398 --> 15:42.066
What are you doing here?

15:44.277 --> 15:45.612
[YUJI] I could ask you that.

15:46.112 --> 15:47.238
Ah.

15:48.072 --> 15:49.908
Ever have the chance
to take a bath

15:49.948 --> 15:51.701
while still fully clothed?

15:51.743 --> 15:52.744
[YUJI] Never.

15:53.703 --> 15:56.915
Surprisingly, it feels better
than I expected it would.

15:59.375 --> 16:00.585
You know...

16:01.669 --> 16:04.046
back when I was
in elementary school,

16:04.088 --> 16:07.341
I loved our safety classes
on swimming in clothes.

16:08.760 --> 16:11.596
So many things have stopped
mattering to me lately.

16:11.970 --> 16:13.264
So I've been challenging myself

16:13.306 --> 16:16.392
to try things I assumed
I shouldn't be doing.

16:16.434 --> 16:18.144
I've basically
gone off the rails

16:18.185 --> 16:19.854
after hitting my mid-30s.

16:19.896 --> 16:21.105
Funny, huh?

16:21.689 --> 16:23.441
I guess it's kind of amusing.

16:24.150 --> 16:25.819
You're Higuruma, right?

16:26.444 --> 16:27.821
In the flesh.

16:27.862 --> 16:28.905
I'm here to talk.

16:29.530 --> 16:31.825
[HIGURUMA] Hold on.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

16:32.325 --> 16:33.952
I happen to be a lawyer.

16:33.992 --> 16:37.121
For 30 minutes,
I charged 5,000 yen to consult.

16:37.163 --> 16:38.581
So either pay up or shut up.

16:38.623 --> 16:39.998
Huh?

16:40.291 --> 16:41.292
[chuckles]

16:41.501 --> 16:42.627
I'm just kidding.

16:42.669 --> 16:44.086
I wanted to see
what it feels like

16:44.128 --> 16:46.380
to be a cutthroat lawyer.
[laughs]

16:47.173 --> 16:48.257
[YUJI] I see.

16:48.758 --> 16:50.510
What's this guy doing?

16:51.469 --> 16:53.554
You still have a hundred points,
don't you?

16:54.347 --> 16:57.057
He's not a past sorcerer
who's been incarnated.

16:57.099 --> 17:00.102
He's a modern sorcerer
whose technique was activated.

17:00.144 --> 17:02.814
We can talk it out.
There's room for negotiation.

17:03.230 --> 17:05.023
[REGGIE] Okay,
you passed the test

17:05.065 --> 17:06.734
- with flying colors.
- [MEGUMI] Huh?

17:06.776 --> 17:09.236
[REGGIE] You've got more
than enough, I can tell.

17:09.278 --> 17:11.447
That's quite the shikigami
you have there.

17:11.489 --> 17:13.073
I bet you're strong.

17:13.115 --> 17:14.868
If you were weak,
I'd just kill you

17:14.909 --> 17:16.327
as another average mark.

17:16.369 --> 17:17.578
But you're good.

17:17.620 --> 17:18.830
Let's work together.

17:18.872 --> 17:21.332
[REMI] What gives?
I didn't agree to this!

17:23.125 --> 17:24.418
[MEGUMI] What are you proposing?

17:25.085 --> 17:27.129
[REGGIE] How much
do you actually know so far

17:27.171 --> 17:28.882
about this Culling Game?

17:29.423 --> 17:30.591
[MEGUMI] It's a ritual.

17:30.925 --> 17:32.050
It uses the cursed energy

17:32.092 --> 17:33.594
of the players
inside the barriers

17:33.636 --> 17:36.054
to ferry the people of Japan
to the other side.

17:36.764 --> 17:39.057
And then changes them
into something inhuman.

17:39.934 --> 17:42.020
Guess I should stay quiet
about Tengen.

17:42.395 --> 17:43.730
[REGGIE] Really?

17:44.146 --> 17:46.106
- Do you know Kenjaku, then?
- [gasps]

17:47.107 --> 17:49.151
[MEGUMI] I knew there had
to be at least one sorcerer

17:49.193 --> 17:51.153
connected to Kenjaku
in this game.

17:52.530 --> 17:53.907
[YUJI] Uh, so,

17:54.240 --> 17:55.449
to be frank,

17:55.867 --> 17:56.993
we need your help.

17:57.368 --> 17:59.037
We wanna stop
the Culling Game.

17:59.579 --> 18:00.872
Uh, time out.

18:00.914 --> 18:02.331
When I say stop the game,

18:02.373 --> 18:04.625
I mean stop
the obligated killing.

18:04.667 --> 18:06.502
If we could use
your hundred points,

18:06.544 --> 18:08.671
we'd be able
to add a new rule to the game.

18:09.047 --> 18:11.131
[HIGURUMA] Permit me
to be frank as well.

18:12.008 --> 18:13.300
I refuse.

18:15.428 --> 18:17.013
[YUJI] Is that another joke?

18:17.055 --> 18:19.515
No. I just sense huge potential

18:19.557 --> 18:21.684
in letting the Culling Game
continue as is.

18:22.018 --> 18:24.020
Sometimes the law is powerless.

18:24.062 --> 18:27.440
However, think about the rules
of this Culling Game.

18:27.481 --> 18:29.859
If the power
I've been granted is real,

18:29.901 --> 18:31.986
then those rules must be, too.

18:32.028 --> 18:33.404
[REGGIE] I think all your talk

18:33.613 --> 18:36.741
about players' cursed energy
being used inside the barriers,

18:36.783 --> 18:38.492
it's probably just a bluff.

18:38.534 --> 18:39.953
[MEGUMI] A bluff?

18:39.994 --> 18:41.370
[REGGIE] Well, less of a bluff,

18:41.412 --> 18:44.373
and more like you're
describing Plan B or C.

18:44.415 --> 18:46.084
Here's three reasons why.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.086
The number of players,

18:48.126 --> 18:50.088
the strength gap
between players,

18:50.128 --> 18:51.756
and the barriers' rules.

18:52.172 --> 18:54.634
If roughly 1,000 people
were equally split up

18:54.675 --> 18:56.343
between the 10 colonies,

18:56.385 --> 18:59.555
that would come out
to 100 people per colony.

19:00.056 --> 19:02.767
However,
among the players are sorcerers

19:02.809 --> 19:04.560
like Kashimo or Higuruma,

19:04.602 --> 19:06.896
who are much stronger
than the rest.

19:06.938 --> 19:08.815
Those two alone
have already culled

19:08.856 --> 19:10.691
60 sorcerers between them.

19:10.733 --> 19:13.069
And I bet you, there's
a sorcerer just like them

19:13.111 --> 19:15.029
in each of the other colonies.

19:15.071 --> 19:17.490
So then, the weak
are weeded out early on.

19:17.531 --> 19:20.118
Does that mean the Culling Game
ends as a stalemate?

19:20.534 --> 19:22.536
He's confirmed my suspicions.

19:22.870 --> 19:24.747
The colony's been too quiet.

19:25.665 --> 19:26.916
It already has.

19:26.958 --> 19:29.919
Well, at least it has
here in Tokyo Number One.

19:29.961 --> 19:32.005
On top of that,
there's the teleportation,

19:32.046 --> 19:33.756
when people enter the colonies.

19:33.798 --> 19:36.174
It serves to spread out players
as they enter the game.

19:36.216 --> 19:38.176
But its main goal
is likely to encourage

19:38.218 --> 19:40.888
an early second awakening
of modern sorcerers.

19:40.930 --> 19:43.808
There are some who die
during the teleportation, too.

19:43.850 --> 19:45.183
Now, if he was really trying

19:45.225 --> 19:46.769
to use the players'
cursed energy,

19:46.853 --> 19:49.313
then he would probably want
the greatest number of sorcerers

19:49.355 --> 19:51.398
to fight
for the longest time possible.

19:51.440 --> 19:54.068
[HIGURUMA] What if people who
broke the rules were punished,

19:54.110 --> 19:55.736
not with the need
of indictments,

19:55.778 --> 19:58.031
prosecutions or arguments
at trials,

19:58.072 --> 19:59.782
but by pure physics instead?

20:00.198 --> 20:01.617
Wouldn't that be wonderful?

20:01.951 --> 20:04.370
I'll grant you, there's issues
with the current rules,

20:04.411 --> 20:05.913
but I wanna watch
over the system

20:05.955 --> 20:07.874
serving as a basis
for this game.

20:08.457 --> 20:10.710
It'll ruin everything
if it ends too soon.

20:11.002 --> 20:13.129
I'd especially love
to witness at least once,

20:13.171 --> 20:14.463
the stripping of a technique

20:14.505 --> 20:16.507
mentioned in rules two
and eight.

20:16.799 --> 20:17.842
And it's better for the rules

20:17.884 --> 20:19.802
if being stripped
means death, too.

20:20.260 --> 20:22.763
The Culling Game itself
is considered a ritual.

20:23.221 --> 20:24.515
If we take too long,

20:24.557 --> 20:26.559
every person in this nation
will die.

20:26.600 --> 20:27.768
That's not true.

20:28.019 --> 20:30.563
The Culling Game insists
on its own ongoing longevity.

20:30.604 --> 20:32.982
[YUJI] I don't really
get that part either!

20:35.693 --> 20:37.235
I'll rephrase it, then.

20:38.278 --> 20:41.407
Let me use your 100 points,
Higuruma!

20:42.575 --> 20:44.535
[HIGURUMA]
Have you ever killed someone

20:44.577 --> 20:46.579
who really ticked you off?

20:46.620 --> 20:48.372
[♪ energetic rock music playing]

20:49.707 --> 20:51.542
Feels better than I expected.

20:52.418 --> 20:54.170
A helluva lot better.

20:55.004 --> 20:56.380
[YUJI] A shikigami?

20:56.672 --> 20:58.549
Higuruma has a hundred points.

20:58.591 --> 21:00.843
He might have killed
20 sorcerers already.

21:01.259 --> 21:03.012
I can't just recklessly jump in.

21:03.429 --> 21:04.722
I'll go on defense.

21:05.139 --> 21:07.850
But I'll be ready
to respond to any attack.

21:10.519 --> 21:12.312
Domain Expansion.

21:12.730 --> 21:14.314
Deadly Sentencing.

21:14.356 --> 21:16.316
[gavel banging]

21:26.869 --> 21:28.913
[REGGIE] The idea
of a rule not hindering

21:28.955 --> 21:30.497
the continuation of the game,

21:30.539 --> 21:32.374
it's just a cover
for the real plan.

21:32.750 --> 21:34.376
Mark my words.

21:34.418 --> 21:36.170
When only the strong remain,

21:36.212 --> 21:39.465
Kenjaku is going to drop a bomb
on this competition.

21:39.506 --> 21:43.177
And the Culling Game
will fulfill its purpose.

21:47.473 --> 21:50.559
[explosion]

22:10.328 --> 22:12.498
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:40.627 --> 23:42.504
[HIGURUMA] Now,
make your argument.

23:42.546 --> 23:43.714
[YUJI]
What if I'm judged guilty?

23:43.756 --> 23:44.882
[HIGURUMA] Judgeman,
please begin.

23:44.924 --> 23:45.925
[YUJI] You mean I can lie?

23:46.342 --> 23:47.385
[HIGURUMA] You get one chance
to make a statement.

23:47.467 --> 23:48.761
[YUJI]
I can't control cursed energy!

23:48.802 --> 23:50.346
[HIGURUMA] How can he
hold his own against me

23:50.388 --> 23:51.597
without cursed energy?

23:51.638 --> 23:52.890
[YUJI] I want a retrial!

23:52.932 --> 23:53.974
One more time!
